    "raw": "# Breisk\n\n*The institute's foothold inside the line — a cleared town turned laboratory.*\n\nProject: [[The Space Between Names|The Space Between Names]]\n\nA coastal town that stood on the western shore of the peninsula before the Boundary came, and was inside the line when it closed. Its people were cleared out at onset; the institute kept the buildings. Breisk is now the institute's principal installation **inside** the Boundary — not a station on the edge of the cordon, but a working town held within it, on the seaward side where the land meets open water.\n\n## Why it holds\n\nBreisk sits where the Boundary fronts the sea, far enough from the deep to be worked and close enough that everything done there is done against the clock of the next hush. It is reached and supplied **by sea**; the landward approaches are watched and thin. That isolation is the point — a site that can be resupplied and, if it comes to it, abandoned by water, without ever opening the cordon.\n\n## What it is for\n\nBreisk is where the institute's work on the Boundary actually happens: monitoring and forecasting, the bunker-labs ([[Nikolai Alexiou|Niko]]'s among them, working the flora off the adjacent coast), and the facility where the collected — material and people — are **processed**. Post-swell collection runs out of here; what the Stilling pushes to the perimeter is brought back to Breisk.\n\n## Who holds it\n\nHeld by the **Containment Security Detachment** (CSD), the institute's standing security arm — distinct from the **Perimeter Security Element**, which works the field and the edge. Breisk answers to **the Director, Sabine Reisz**. Proximity to the Boundary is itself a hazard, so personnel rotate under exposure limits; no one stays at Breisk longer than the institute's own rules allow.\n\n## To develop\n\n- The original town: its harbour, what it was before, who still remembers it as home.\n- The processing facility: what \"processed\" means, and where the line runs between research and harm.\n- Breisk in the plot: it is where [[Ime Baardo|Ime]] would have been taken had Niko called her in — the place he chose not to deliver her to.\n",
