    "raw": "# Virelsk\n\n*The country the Boundary happened to.*\n\nProject: [[The Space Between Names|The Space Between Names]]\n\nThe sovereign state within whose territory the Boundary lies. [[The Boundary|De Râne]] is a volcanic peninsula of Virelsk's northern coast — a tongue of land reaching into the sea, severed from the mainland by the cordon drawn across its neck. The peninsula was Virelsk's before it was anything else; the people of [[Eirskel]] who named it *De Râne* speak Virelsk, and the displaced of it — [[Ime Baardo|Ime]], [[Senn Baardo|Senn]] — are Virelskan nationals.\n\n## Jurisdiction\n\nVirelsk holds the land, but not what the land became. It admits the institute under an intergovernmental mandate and enforces the lockdown of Eirskel at the cordon, while withholding any public acknowledgement of what the Boundary is. The official posture is containment and secrecy: a sealed peninsula, an evacuation that never quite ended, a research presence no one names.\n\n## Geography\n\nOceanic and volcanic country, mild and fogbound along the northern coast. The peninsula rises off the mainland and points out to sea; the cordon runs across its narrow neck, and beyond the neck the land is ordinary Virelsk. [[Kalliros]] lies across the water — a separate state, the country [[Nikolai Alexiou|Niko]] came from.\n\n## To develop\n\n- The capital and the seat of government; how far the secrecy reaches inside Virelsk itself.\n- Relations with [[Kalliros]] and the other states party to the institute's mandate.\n- What ordinary Virelskans are told the cordon is for.\n",
